review_thoughts: I have struggled for a long time to find a daily SPF that I love. I'm a fair redhead and am adamant about protecting my skin, but it's always been that skincare step that I just kind of groan about but do it because I have to. After trying, and loving, a number of other Skinceuticals products, I decided to give this one a try. I think I may have struck gold! The texture is thin and watery, but I squeeze a generous amount onto my fingertips and layer every morning on top of my CE Ferulic. It feels almost oily at first, but soaks in beautifully if you give it a minute. I have had no issues with my liquid foundation on top of this, no pilling or other texture concerns. The only issue I run into is having more of a sheen on my face throughout the day, but a dusting of powder is a quick fix. When camping or running around outside I'm sure I could wear this alone, but just out of habit I tend to still put foundation on top. I don't personally find that the tint is noticeable. I love to sample skincare and try new products so I'm sure I'll be testing out some more SPF products, but I'm certain that this one will always have a place in my arsenal.

review_thoughts: This is a fantastic product - love that there are so many skincare benefits in one product. My skin is fairly dry and I apply this after an antioxidant serum and I don't need additional moisture. If I'm feeling drier, I'll use the Vichy Mineral 89 underneath for a little light quench. (I did try it once with my usual moisturizer first and it felt like too much.)
